'''Brian Gutiérrez''' (born 17 June 2003) is a professional [[soccer|football]] player who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]]. Born in the United States, he plays for the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Club career==
===Chicago Fire===
Born in [[Berwyn, Illinois]], U.S., Gutiérrez began his career with the [[Chicago Fire FC|Chicago Fire]] youth academy in 2015.<ref name="signed">{{cite news |last1=McCraney |first1=Patrick |title=Chicago Fire sign academy midfielder Brian Gutiérrez |url=https://www.hottimeinoldtown.com/2020/3/9/21171562/chicago-fire-sign-academy-midfielder-brian-gutierrez |access-date=4 April 2021 |publisher=Hot Time in Old Town |date=9 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March 2020, Gutiérrez signed a [[Homegrown Player Rule (Major League Soccer)|homegrown player]] deal with the club's first team in [[Major League Soccer]].<ref name="signed"/>

Gutiérrez made his professional debut for the Chicago Fire on 20 August 2020, against [[Columbus Crew]], coming on as an 82nd-minute substitute in a 3–0 defeat.<ref>{{cite web |title=Columbus Crew 3–0 Chicago Fire |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/08/21/united-states/mls/columbus-crew/chicago-fire/3333275/ |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

===Guadalajara===
On 12 December 2025, Gutiérrez joined Mexican club [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]] for a reported fee of $5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chicagofirefc.com/news/chicago-fire-fc-transfers-homegrown-midfielder-brian-gutierrez-to-historic-mexican-side-club-deportivo-guadalajara |title=Chicago Fire FC Transfers Homegrown Midfielder Brian Gutiérrez to Historic Mexican Side Club Deportivo Guadalajara |publisher=Chicago Fire Football Club |date=12 December 2025}}</ref> He made his [[Liga MX]] debut on 10 January 2026 in a home match against [[C.F. Pachuca|Pachuca]] as a starter, contributing an assist at the 17th minute for the first goal of a 2–0 home victory.<ref>https://www.soyfutbol.com/en/news/chivas-ignites-the-2026-clausura-brian-gutierrez-debuts-in-style-and-sparks-rojiblanca-excitement-20260111-0049.html</ref>

==International career==
===United States===
Gutiérrez has played for the [[United States Soccer Federation#Youth national teams|US youth national teams]] at multiple levels, including the [[United States men's national under-20 soccer team|under-20 team]]. He was also in consideration for the [[United States men's national soccer team|USMNT]]'s senior camp in December 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=Berhalter's 26-player December camp roster mixes veterans and youth |url=http://www.americansoccernow.com/articles/berhalter-s-december-camp-roster-mixes-veterans-and-youth |website=American Soccer Now}}</ref> On 8 October 2023, Gutiérrez was called up to the [[United States men's national under-23 soccer team|under-23 team]] ahead of [[Exhibition game|friendlies]] against [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico]] and [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Twenty-three Players Called to U.S. Olympic Men's Soccer Team Training Camp as Preparations for Paris 2024 Kick Off in Phoenix |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2023/10/23-players-called-to-us-olympic-mens-soccer-team-training-camp |website=ussoccer.com |access-date=8 October 2023 |date=8 October 2023}}</ref>

In January 2025, Gutiérrez played two friendly matches for the senior United States, against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] and [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2026}}

===Switch to Mexico national team===
On 6 November 2025, Gutierrez’s management announced the player was considering switching to the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Cleveland |first=Parker |title=Brian Gutiérrez reportedly wants to play for Mexico |url=https://www.starsandstripesfc.com/latest-news/41167/usmnt-midfielder-brian-gutierrez-reportedly-wants-to-play-for-mexico|access-date=5 November 2025 |publisher=Stars and Stripes FC |date=7 November 2025}}</ref>

On 15 January 2026, Gutiérrez was called up by Mexico and appeared in a friendly match against [[Panama national football team|Panama]] on 22 January, the same day that [[FIFA]] officials authorized his allegiance [[List of association football players capped by two senior national teams|switch]] to Mexico.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hernández |first=Cesar |title=Mexico calls up dual-nationals Richard Ledezma, Brian Gutiérrez |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47623526/mexico-calls-dual-nationals-ledezma-gutierrez|access-date=15 January 2026 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=15 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 January 2026 |title=Richard Ledezma, Brian Gutiérrez complete U.S. switch to Mexico |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47677347/richard-ledezma-brian-gutierrez-complete-us-switch-mexico |access-date=23 January 2026 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On 25 February 2026, Gutierréz scored his first goal for Mexico in a friendly match against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] in stoppage time as Mexico took the 4–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/401842389/iceland-mexico |title=Mexico 4–0 Iceland |date=25 February 2026 |work=[[ESPN]]|access-date=25 February 2026}}</ref>

On 28 April 2026, Brian Gutiérrez was included on the Mexico national team’s first 12-player roster that will take part in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]]. On 31 May 2026, he is officially confirmed listed on the Mexican national team’s World Cup roster.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |title=Las Chivas mandan en la Selección Mexicana – El equipo más mexicano lidera con el mayor número de elementos en esta primera lista de Javier Aguirre rumbo al Mundial 2026. |url=https://www.telemundo.com/deportes/copa-mundial-de-la-fifa-2026/las-chivas-mandan-en-la-seleccion-mexicana-rcna342510 |lang=es|access-date=28 April 2026 |publisher=[[Telemundo]] |date=28 April 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in the United States, Gutiérrez is of [[Mexican Americans|Mexican]] descent through both of his parents, who are originally from [[Jalisco]]. He obtained his Mexican citizenship in November 2025, making him eligible to play for the Mexico national team.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://chasingacup.com/2022-youth-series-top-20-born-in-2003/ |title=2022 Youth Series: Top 20 Born In 2003 |first=Marcus |last=Chairez |date=8 August 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gonzalez |first=Diego |title=¡OFICIAL! Brian Gutiérrez ya tiene su pasaporte mexicano y eso lo habilita para algo más que la Selección Nacional |lang=es |url=https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecadeportes/oficial-brian-gutierrez-ya-tiene-pasaporte-mexicano-habilita-para-algo-mas|access-date=6 November 2025 |publisher=[[TV Azteca]] |date=6 November 2025}}</ref>

